      "chunk_index": 1,
      "summary": "Here's a concise step-by-step guide on how to make pizza at home:\n\nDough (makes 2–3 pizzas):\n\nIngredients: 500g flour (bread or all-purpose), 300–350ml warm water, 2 tsp instant yeast, 2 tsp salt, 2 tbsp olive oil.\n\nMethod:\n\nMix dry ingredients (flour, yeast, salt).\n\nAdd water and olive oil, stir until shaggy dough forms.\n\nKnead for 8-10 minutes until smooth and elastic.\n\nCover and let rise 1-2 hours at room temperature, or refrigerate overnight for better flavor.\n\nSauce:\n\nIngredients: 1 can (400g) crushed tomatoes, 1–2 minced garlic cloves, 1 tsp dried oregano, pinch of sugar (optional), salt, pepper.\n\nMethod: Mix all ingredients cold; no cooking required.\n\nAssembling:\n\nPreheat oven to its highest setting (475–550°F / 245–290°C). Use a pizza stone or baking sheet.\n\nPunch down dough, divide into balls, and let rest 15-20 minutes.\n\nStretch dough into thin rounds (avoid rolling pin for a fluffier crust).\n\nSpread a thin layer of sauce, add desired toppings (cheese, veggies, meats).\n\nBaking:\n\nBake for 7–10 minutes until crust is golden and toppings are bubbly.\n\nOptional: for a crispier crust, use bread flour and let the dough ferment in the fridge for 24–48 hours.\n\nEnjoy your homemade pizza!"
    },
