      "chunk_index": 2,
      "summary": "Here’s a concise step-by-step guide to make pizza at home:\n\nPrepare the dough:\n\nMix 1 cup warm water (105–110°F / 40–43°C) with 1 tsp yeast and 1 tsp sugar. Let proof 5 min if using active dry yeast.\n\nStir in 2 cups flour, 1 tsp salt, knead 6–8 min by hand until smooth.\n\nCoat with oil, cover, and let rise 60–90 min until doubled.\n\nDivide into 2 balls, rest 15–20 min before shaping.\n\nMake the sauce:\n\nCombine 14–15 oz crushed tomatoes, 1–2 minced garlic cloves (or 1 tsp garlic powder), 1–2 tbsp olive oil, 1 tsp dried oregano, ½ tsp dried basil, and optional ½ tsp sugar. Stir well; no cooking needed.\n\nAssemble the pizza:\n\nPreheat oven to 475°F (245°C).\n\nStretch dough into discs, place on a floured or oiled surface/pizza stone.\n\nSpread sauce, add cheese and toppings.\n\nBake:\n\nCook 12–15 min until crust is golden and cheese bubbly.\n\nLet rest 2–3 min before slicing.\n\nTips:\n\nFor a crispier crust, use bread flour or a 60/40 mix with whole-wheat, and target 65–70% hydration.\n\nAdjust toppings sparingly to avoid soggy pizza.\n\nThis gives a practical, no-frills approach that works reliably at home."
    }
  ]
